Ok! Several other remarks:
 - It's not (at least completely) secp256k1 anymore;
 - You should probably say something about the neutral element (0) of the group law;
 - You should not use 2 different P (I know, one of them is blue ;-) , but still);
 - You should explicitly mention that P (the blue one ;-) ) is prime.
(And, just for your information, to compute the modular inverse of x mod P when P is prime, you can simply use pow(x,P-2,P) to compute x^(P-2) = x^(-1) mod P by Fermat's little theorem.)
